==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Galiot
<hw>Gal"i*ot</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>galiote</ets>, F. <ets>galiote</ets>. See <er>Galley</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Naut.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A small galley, formerly used in
the Mediterranean, built mainly for speed. It was moved both by sails
and oars, having one mast, and sixteen or twenty seats for rowers.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>A strong, light-draft, Dutch merchant vessel, carrying
a mainmast and a mizzenmast, and a large gaff mainsail.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Galipot</ent>⟦br⟧
